The SpeechChoice (12) type is used to apply settings to SpeechContext lines.

The type is used to determine under what circumstances the line can be triggered and
how frequently it can be used.


Fields:

Field name  Type      FileRef Description
--
Name        metahash  dat151  SpeechChoice name from Dat151SpeechContext <Unk09>.
Flags       flags             Unknown flags
Unk01       metahash          Unknown
Unk02       integer           Unknown //min time in ms between repeat?
Unk03       integer           Unknown //max time in ms between repeat?
Unk04       byte              Unknown
Unk05       byte              Unknown
Unk06       byte              Unknown
Unk07       byte              Unknown
Unk08       metahash          Unknown
Unk09       metahash          Unknown
Unk10       byte              Unknown
Unk11       byte              Unknown
Unk12       byte              Unknown
Unk13       byte              Unknown
Unk14       byte              Unknown //only when Unk11 > 2 generic_whatever_sc
Unk15       byte              Unknown //only when Unk11 > 2 generic_whatever_sc
Unk16       byte              Unknown //only when Unk11 > 2 generic_whatever_sc
Unk17       byte              Unknown //only when Unk11 > 2 generic_whatever_sc




Examples:

<Item type="SpeechChoice" ntOffset="282264">
 <Name>generic_insult_high_sc</Name>
 <Flags value="0xAAA94401" />
 <Unk01>hash_5B2027A1</Unk01>
 <Unk02 value="5000" />
 <Unk03 value="10000" />
 <Unk04 value="1" />
 <Unk05 value="0" />
 <Unk06 value="0" />
 <Unk07 value="0" />
 <Unk08 />
 <Unk09 />
 <Unk10 value="3" />
 <Unk11 value="1" />
 <Unk12 value="22" />
 <Unk13 value="0" />
</Item>